{
  "texts": [
    "For example, in creating wordclouds and N-grams, to ensure consistent analysis, all titles were converted (a) Distribution of Words (b) Distribution of Characters Figure 7: Distribution of words and characters for news headlines in our datasetto lowercase and stripped of non-alphabetic characters like punctuation and symbols.",
    "Titles were then converted to a corpora of individual words from which common stop-words were excluded.",
    "Additionally, domain-specific stop words like \"AI\" and \"ML\" were removed to focus on more significant terms.",
    "We applied standard stop-words available from Python libraries, and we also applied custom stop-words based on irrelevance, commonality and error at multiple points to ensure that the most relevant words and phrases are visible.",
    "Terms like \"stock\" and \"buy\" were also excluded from the overall n-gram analysis.Named Entity Recognition (NER) Analysis: NER analysis helped us identify the top individuals, companies, locations and items mentioned in the news headlines."
  ]
}